docs.lead_paragraph: The largest gains in the export trade of the United States in March were in exports to Asia, which increased from $32,570,000 in March, 1936, to $52,972,000, according to the monthly study of exports and imports made public today by the Department of Commerce.

docs.lead_paragraph: Bond values continued yesterday to drift irregularly to slightly lower levels in another day of uninspired trading on the New York Stock Exchange. Although prices of the higher grade corporate issues held within a narrow trading range, the improvement shown in the stock market was not, to any noticeable extent, reflected in the market for fixed-interest-bearing securities.

docs.snippet: Secretary Morgenthau of the Treasury Department made it clear to associates today that he was unequivocally opposed to general international monetary conferences, believing that nothing could be accomplished by them.
